text: Gnathoenia flavovariegata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Stephan von Breuning in 1935. It is known from the Ivory Coast, Ghana, and Sierra Leone.BioLib.cz - Gnathoenia flavovariegata. Retrieved on 8 September 2014. ==References== Category:Ceroplesini Category:Beetles described in 1935
